The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Srinagar, Aug. 16: Two army officers and a jawan were killed when their chopper crashed into a mountain because of bad weather, soon after it had taken off for a rescue mission in the Ladakh sector.           
	The helicopter had two pilots, Major Padmanabhan and Major S. Ganapathy, and jawan E. Narsaih from the aviation squadron on board.                   
	 Shimla: A flood alert has been sounded in three Himachal Pradesh districts  Kinnaur, Shimla and Bilaspur  after heavy rain for a week. Residents have been told to move to safer areas as the Sutlej is in spate, chief minister Prem Kumar Dhumal said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The National Tiger Conservation Authority has released a compensation package of Rs 52 crore to expedite relocation of villagers from tiger parks. A major chunk  Rs 19-crore  of the package has gone to the Sariska sanctuary.                  
	 Chandigarh (PTI): The local administration allowed liquor vendors to open shutters after 5pm on Independence Day, in a departure from the full dry day tradition, officials said on Saturday.                                                                                                                         
